dcterms:description: A large annotated corpus for learning natural language inference, containing 570K human-written English sentence pairs manually labeled by multiple human subjects, indicating whether the premise entails, contradicts, or has no inference relation with the hypothesis.
dcterms:title: Stanford Natural Language Inference (SNLI) dataset
